article.headline: Colgate 84, Cornell 77 (OT)
article.story: ITHACA, N.Y. (AP) -- Mark Linebaugh scored 23 points and Alvin Reed added 17 to lift Colgate to an 84-77 overtime victory over Cornell Tuesday. Colgate hit all eight free throws in overtime and was 19-of-20 from the line for the game. Andrew Zidar added 16 points and 12 rebounds for Colgate (1-1). Cornell (0-2) rallied from a 10-point deficit and took the lead with 12:41 left in the game on a three-pointer by Cody Toppert. The lead changed several times down the stretch but the game ended tied at 69 after Cornell's Eric Taylor converted a three-point play with 1:54 remaining. Colgate scored the first seven points in overtime with Linebaugh hitting all four of his free throws. Gabe Stephenson had 17 points and 12 rebounds for Cornell (0-2). Toppert had 16 points and Ka'Ron Barnes added 15.
